EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to workforce development; providing for the
creation of the Southern Nevada Health Care Workforce
Apprenticeship Pilot Program; making an appropriation;
and providing other matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law provides for the promotion, registration and approval of
2 apprenticeship programs in this State. (Chapter 610 of NRS) Section 1 of this bill
3 requires the Department of Business and Industry to develop, create and administer
4 the Southern Nevada Health Care Workforce Apprenticeship Pilot Program for the
5 purpose of addressing shortages in the number of medical assistants and
6 pharmaceutical technicians in this State through the establishment of apprenticeship
7 programs in Southern Nevada for the training of such persons. Section 1 requires
8 the Program to provide: (1) for the establishment of apprenticeship programs in
9 Southern Nevada for the training of medical assistants and pharmaceutical
10 technicians, which must be registered and approved by the State Apprenticeship
11 Council; and (2) money to participants in the program to cover the costs of
12 participating in the program, including, without limitation, fees for professional
13 certifications and registrations, as applicable, for not more than 100 apprentices
14 who are enrolled in apprenticeship programs established under the Program.
15 Section 2 of this bill makes an appropriation to the Department of Business and
16 Industry to carry out the Program.
