THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. 1. The Department of Business and Industry shall
2 develop, create and administer the Southern Nevada Health Care
3 Workforce Apprenticeship Pilot Program for the purpose of
4 addressing shortages in the number of medical assistants and
5 pharmaceutical technicians in this State through the establishment of
6 apprenticeship programs for the training of such persons.
7 2. The Program must provide:
8 (a) For the establishment of apprenticeship programs in
9 Southern Nevada for the training of medical assistants and
10 pharmaceutical technicians. Any apprenticeship program established
11 under the Program must be registered and approved by the State
12 Apprenticeship Council pursuant to chapter 610 of NRS.
13 (b) Money to participants in the Program to cover the costs of
14 participating in the Program, including, without limitation, fees for
15 professional certifications and registrations, as applicable, for not
16 more than 100 apprentices who are enrolled in apprenticeship
17 programs established under the Program.
18 3. As used in this section:
19 (a) “Medical assistant” has the meaning ascribed to it in NRS
20 630.0129 and 633.075.
21 (b) “Pharmaceutical technician” has the meaning ascribed to it
22 in NRS 639.0113.
23 Sec. 2. 1. There is hereby appropriated from the State
24 General Fund to the Department of Business and Industry the sum
25 of $300,000 to carry out the Southern Nevada Health Care
26 Workforce Apprenticeship Pilot Program established pursuant to
27 section 1 of this act.
28 2. Any remaining balance of the appropriation made by
29 subsection 1 must not be committed for expenditure after June 30,
30 2027, by the entity to which the appropriation is made or any entity
31 to which money from the appropriation is granted or otherwise
32 transferred in any manner, and any portion of the appropriated
33 money remaining must not be spent for any purpose after
34 September 17, 2027, by either the entity to which the money was
35 appropriated or the entity to which the money was subsequently
36 granted or transferred, and must be reverted to the State General
37 Fund on or before September 17, 2027.
38 Sec. 3. This act becomes effective on July 1, 2025.
